    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for the rename feature. It touches **5 files** with no new imports needed anywhere:\n\n---\n\n### What gets added and where\n\n**`api/types.go`** (after line 765 — end of `CopyRequest`)\nAdd `RenameRequest` — identical shape to `CopyRequest` with `Source` and `Destination` JSON fields.\n\n**`api/client.go`** (after line 387 — end of `Copy`)\nAdd `Client.Rename` — mirrors `Copy` exactly: POST to `/api/rename`, no response body.\n\n**`server/images.go`** (after line 434 — end of `CopyModel`)\nAdd `RenameModel(src, dst model.Name) error` — the core logic:\n1. Validate both names are fully qualified\n2. Call `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → return `os.ErrNotExist` if source missing (→ 404)\n3. Call `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` → return `os.ErrExist` if destination already present (→ 409)\n4. Call `CopyModel(src, dst)` to write the new manifest\n5. Call `srcManifest.Remove()` to delete the old manifest file\n6. Call `srcManifest.RemoveLayers()` — **safe** because `RemoveLayers` re-scans all on-disk manifests to build its in-use set; since dst was just written, the shared blobs are protected and never deleted\n\n**`server/routes.go`**\n- Add `RenameHandler` after `CopyHandler` (line 1483) — same validation pattern as `CopyHandler`, dispatching errors to 404/409/500\n- Add `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` after the copy route (line 1698)\n\n**`cmd/cmd.go`**\n- Add `RenameHandler` func after `CopyHandler` (line 1350)\n- Add `renameCmd` cobra command after `copyCmd` (line 2263): `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `Args: cobra.ExactArgs(2)`, `PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat`\n- Add `renameCmd` to the env-docs loop and to `rootCmd.AddCommand`",
